		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">I propose to develop comprehensive theoretical model for electro- optical properties material with QD consequently from a microscopic point of view.  The model will be based on well established material parameters of strained GaAs/InAs composition.  The main aim of the proposed work is to improve understanding of the fundamental optoelectronic properties of self organised QDs.  The proposed theoretical study will be closely associated with current experimental investigation of QDs and carried out in conjunction with a co-ordinated program of optical spectroscopy, electrical transport, growth research and structural analysis of QDs.  Besides fundamental study of OD system attention will be addressed to the theory of real self assembled QDs taking into consideration their environment.  The key steps of this proposal include calculation of energy levels for electrons and holes in the QD and computation of times of intersubband scattering, trapping and escape.  The resulting kinetic and equation will model various experiments with QD material such as photoluminescence, electro-adsorption, and time dependent spectroscopy.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
